---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const standards = [
  { k: "SOURCING", t: "Claims carry receipts", d: "If we say a launch worked, we link the numbers. If we cite a framework, we show the example. Thought leadership without evidence is just confident guessing." },
  { k: "BREVITY", t: "Your time is the product", d: "The whole promise is compression. If a sentence isn't pulling its weight, it's cut before it reaches you. A brief that takes twenty minutes isn't a brief." },
  { k: "STANCE", t: "We take a position", d: "Neutrality is a way of saying nothing at length. You'll get a clear point of view - and the reasoning behind it, so you can disagree productively." },
  { k: "INDEPENDENCE", t: "No pay-to-play", d: "Sponsors don't pick the stories and never will. When something's an ad, it's stamped as one. Trust is the only asset a brief has." },
];
---

<Layout title="Editorial Standard — Strictly FYI" description="What Strictly FYI is, who it's for, and the standard every filing is held to.">
  <section class="ab-hero">
    <div class="wrap-narrow">
      <p class="tag tag-signal">// the editorial standard</p>
      <h1>Most marketing content is <span class="redact" title="say it louder">noise dressed as insight</span>.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Strictly FYI is the correction. A tight, opinionated go-to-market brief for
        product marketers and founders who are done skimming 2,000-word posts to find
        the one useful paragraph.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap-narrow story">
      <p>
        Here's the problem. The go-to-market world produces an ocean of content -
        threads, newsletters, "ultimate guides," conference talks - and maybe five percent
        of it changes what you'd actually do on Monday. The rest is noise: recycled frameworks,
        engagement bait, and takes so hedged they mean nothing.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Strictly FYI does the filtering.</strong> Every week we read the firehose so
        you don't have to, and file back the handful of things that genuinely matter for
        positioning, launches, and messaging - with a point of view, with sources, and short
        enough to finish before your coffee gets cold.
      </p>
      <blockquote>
        The value isn't in what we include. It's in the ninety-five percent we cut.
      </blockquote>
      <p>
        No gated PDFs. No "let's hop on a quick call." No influencer theatre. Just the brief -
        strictly for your information.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section std-section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="sec-head reveal">
        <p class="tag tag-signal">// what every filing is held to</p>
        <h2>The four standards.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="std-grid">
        {standards.map((s) => (
          <div class="std reveal">
            <span class="std-k mono">{s.k}</span>
            <h3>{s.t}</h3>
            <p>{s.d}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap-narrow who">
      <p class="tag tag-signal">// clearance requirements</p>
      <h2>Who this is for.</h2>
      <ul class="who-list mono">
        <li><span>✓</span> Product marketers who own positioning and launches</li>
        <li><span>✓</span> Founders doing GTM themselves and short on time</li>
        <li><span>✓</span> Growth &amp; demand folks who need the PMM view</li>
        <li><span class="no">✕</span> Anyone looking for "10 ChatGPT prompts to 10x your funnel"</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/#subscribe" class="btn btn-signal">Request access →</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .ab-hero { padding: clamp(3.5rem, 9vw, 6rem) 0 1rem; }
  .ab-hero h1 { font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 6vw, 4rem); line-height: 1.02; margin-top: 0.6rem; }
  .ab-hero .lede { font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--muted); margin-top: 1.4rem; max-width: 58ch; }
  .story p { font-size: 1.12rem; line-height: 1.75; margin: 1.2rem 0; color: #cfcfd4; }
  .story strong { color: var(--ink); }
  .story blockquote { font-family: var(--grotesk); font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 4vw, 2rem); line-height: 1.25; color: var(--signal); text-align: center; margin: 2.5rem 0; padding: 0 1rem; border: none; }
  .sec-head h2 { font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4.5vw, 2.8rem); margin-top: 0.5rem; }
  .std-section { background: var(--panel); border-block: 1px solid var(--line); }
  .std-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 1px; background: var(--line); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: var(--radius); overflow: hidden; }
  .std { background: var(--bg); padding: 2rem 1.8rem; }
  .std-k { color: var(--signal); font-size: 0.72rem; letter-spacing: 0.14em; }
  .std h3 { font-size: 1.3rem; margin: 0.6rem 0 0.5rem; }
  .std p { color: var(--muted); }
  .who h2 { font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 5vw, 2.6rem); margin: 0.4rem 0 1.4rem; }
  .who-list { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.8rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; font-size: 0.98rem; }
  .who-list li { display: flex; gap: 0.7rem; align-items: baseline; color: #cfcfd4; }
  .who-list span { color: var(--signal); font-weight: 700; }
  .who-list .no { color: var(--danger); }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .std-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
</style>
